Ian,<br><br>
I admit I am very cynical on the prospects of any &quot;accomplishment&quot; of substance, regardless of the credentials of any individual. <br><br>
The fact remains that the people of Vietnam are under subjugation by the usual and customary &quot;mind control&quot; doctrine enforced through terror and &quot;re-education&quot; by a not so unusual &quot;peoples republic&quot; whose sole existence is to perpetuate the lifestyles of those in power.<br><br>
To think that there will be a renaissance in the philosophy of the individuals now running Vietnam is to believe that &quot;Queen for a Day&quot; continues as a deep and socially significant event in the lives of the American television viewing public.<br><br>
Having lost one year, fifteen days, eight hours, and ten minutes of my life in 1969/1970 in combat in Vietnam, witnessing the incompetant prosecution of that conflict, and surviving to enjoy the &quot;gift that keeps on giving&quot; conferred by my participation, I view these current events as just another episode of political flim-flam in the continuing vortex of the Vietnam experience.<br><br>
The creation and enforcement of a &quot;state run Buddhist religion&quot; in Vietnam is a sure indicator of the intentions of the present Vietnam government to employ a double standard in its affairs. What else can you expect? They certainly are not going to respect a relationship with a power that failed to flaten them when we had every opportunity to do so 25 to 30 years ago.<br><br>
I am sure that the government of Vietnam will be perfectly willing to tell us what we want to hear, and show us what we want to see, for money.  After all, that is where this latest love-in is headed, isn't it? Cheap sneakers seem to run the world these days.<br><br>
We have but to review the history of Joseph Stalin, Adolph Hitler, and like individuals since to appreciate the strategy of the tactical lie. We can expect nothing less of those presently in power in Vietnam.<br><br>
&quot;Peace in our time&quot;? <br><br>
I sincerely hope I am wrong, but my guts tell me otherwise.<br><br>
Art <br><br>
    
